JOHANNESBURG – President Cyril Ramaphosa has addressed the continued fuel price hikes. Ramaphosa says South Africa is subject to the Rand-Dollar exchange. “South Africa is in an unfortunate position in that we import our energy resource which is oil,” Ramaphosa said. READ: ANC calls on government to freeze fuel hikes “So we are in the end, subject to the price fluctuations that keep on happening on a dollar exchange basis, as well as the price of oil itself…..the difficulties our people are going through at the moment.” Petrol prices in Gauteng soared to R16, 00 a litre this week. Economists are warning of more fuel price increases next month. eNCA